componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText1
componentInstanceProperties.value:
EnGeneIC is a Sydney-based biopharmaceutical company focused on its proprietary EDV™ (EnGeneIC Dream Vector) nanocell platform enabling the targeted delivery of chemotherapeutics and functional nucleic acids in cancer.

By partnering with VentureCrowd, the team at EnGeneIC enjoyed an easy, seamless capital-raise experience - and exceeded its target by 4 million dollars.

Learn more

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText2
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Our Cow, from zero to $10 million in revenue!

"Our Cow grew so quickly to the point where we knew there was potential in the marketplace for it to continue to grow" - Bianca Tarrant

Recently raising over $2 million through over 1,000 investors on the VentureCrowd platform, Our Cow are embarking on the next stage of their business growth.

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText3
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Nexba has raised over $6M across Series A and Series B rounds. In FY17 the company had gross revenue of $2.5M with VentureCrowd investors investing at a pre-money valuation of $20M. Since then, VentureCrowd has raised 2 additional rounds of capital for Nexba.

In FY21 the company had grown to $35M gross revenue and is forecast to nearly double again in FY22. Nexba’s naturally sugar-free sweetener formula has removed over 5 billion grams of sugar from consumers’ diets.

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText4
componentInstanceProperties.value:
4DMedical is a global medical technology company aiming to change the outcome for patients with lung disease by revolutionizing respiratory imaging and ventilation analysis.

VentureCrowd investors were able to invest in the early funding of this MedTech venture, acquiring shares at $0.37. Only 18 months after 4DMedical raised capital through VentureCrowd, they listed on the ASX at $1.50 per share, delivering a 297% return to VentureCrowd investors.

Today, 4DMedical continues to improve global health by providing unique and non-invasive imaging technologies that enable unprecedented insight into pulmonary functioning, critical in the analysis and management of respiratory diseases.

componentInstanceProperties.value:
As your business grows, so does your community, creating a uniquely connected network of followers ready to help you fund your business at every stage of growth from your seed round to your IPO. We are well versed in the varying requirements of companies as they move from incorporating their business to deliver on their purpose, through varying capital raising until an exit event occurs, be that a public listing, trade sale or another M&A event.

Our Investment Management team works closely with the founders to structure the most appropriate deal, from the type of instrument to be used to the term sheet specifications, as appropriate.

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText1
componentInstanceProperties.value:
"Before we worked with VentureCrowd, we had not raised capital officially. However, we did go on the TV show Sharktank which aired back in 2017.

The VentureCrowd team were extremely positive, professional and supportive throughout the entire process. The experience was nerve-wracking but totally exhilarating and well worth it.

We successfully raised funds that will enable us to invest in new marketing channels, including a TV and digital channel opportunity which will provide huge brand exposure for Be Fit Food. You can have the best product in the world but if no one knows about it, then it can never reach its full potential.

A huge thank you to the entire team at VentureCrowd who backed us from Day 1 to make this raise possible."

– Be Fit Food CEO & Founder, Kate Save

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText3

componentInstanceProperties.name: DescriptionText4
componentInstanceProperties.value:
"Raising with the VentureCrowd platform was such an easy, seamless experience and we are thrilled that the team were able to generate so much interest in the raise. Due Diligence was thorough but accomplished rapidly, and the Fireside chat with a presentation and the chance for investors to ask questions was particularly useful and interesting. This investment will assist in funding our clinical program, allowing EnGeneIC to have a significant impact on late-stage cancer patients as well as trialling our novel COVID EDV vaccine.”

– EnGeneIC Co-CEO, Dr. Jennifer MacDiarmid and Dr. Himanshu Brahmbhatt
